      • assertEquals

        public static void assertEquals(long expect,
                long actual)
        Verifies that two values are equal. If the values are not equal a message and stack trace is printed using the printStackTrace method of java.lang.Throwable. The message must be:

           "Error: Expected X, found Y"

        where X and Y are replace with the specified expect and actual values.
        Parameters:
        expect - The expected value.
        actual - The actual value to verify as equal.

      • assertEquals

        public static void assertEquals(double expect,
                double actual,
                double epsilon)
        Verifies that two values are equal within a specified range. If the values are not equal a message and stack trace is printed using the printStackTrace method of java.lang.Throwable. The message must be:

           "Error: Expected X +/-E, found Y"

        where X, E, and Y are replace with the specified expect, epsilon, and actual values, respectively.
        Parameters:
        expect - The expected value.
        actual - The actual value to verify as equal.
        epsilon - The maximum difference allowed between expect and actual for them to be considered equal.

      • assertEqualsObject

        public static void assertEqualsObject(java.lang.Object expect,
                      java.lang.Object actual)
        Verifies that two objects are equal as determined by their equals method. If the values are not equal a message and stack trace is printed using the printStackTrace method of java.lang.Throwable. The message must be:

           "Error: Expected object equality, found inequality"
        Parameters:
        expect - The expected object reference - must NOT be null.
        actual - The actual object reference to verify as equal - may be null.

      • assertEqualsReference

        public static void assertEqualsReference(java.lang.Object expect,
                         java.lang.Object actual)
        Verifies that two references are equal. If the reference are not equal a message and stack trace is printed using the printStackTrace method of java.lang.Throwable. The message must be:

           "Error: Expected reference equality, found inequality"
        Parameters:
        expect - The expected reference value.
        actual - The actual reference value to verify as equal.

      • assertNull

        public static void assertNull(java.lang.Object actual)

           "Error: Expected null, found non-null"
        Parameters:

      • assertNotNull

      • fail

        public static void fail()

           "Error: Explicit failure"
